Responsibilities:


Execute dealing orders for global securities and futures market;
Handle daily phone/online enquiries and perform clients’ account instructions;
Monitor client’s orders and margin level, conduct margin call when necessary;
Match daily transaction records and trade position and compile various trading reports;
Assist in daily operation of dealing room and ad hoc duties. 

Requirement & Qualifications:


Holder of SFC license RA1 and RA2 is an advantage;
Minimum 1 year relevant experience in stocks, futures & options;
General knowledge in global stocks and futures trading;
Familiar with Sharp Point system is a plus;
Good team player, able to work under pressure and willing to learn;
Problem-solving skills and customer-oriented;
Good command of spoken and written English and Chinese including Putonghua;
Willing to work night shift from 4:30pm-1:00am or 12:15am-8:45am with allowance (HK$4,000);
Candidates with more experience will be considered as Senior officer.

 We Offer:

Competitive remuneration package
5 Days Work & Bank Holidays
Attendance Bonus
Meal Allowance
Discretionary Bonus
Medical Insurance
On the Job Training

We provide attractive remuneration package and fringe benefits for the right candidate.

Interested parties please send detailed resume with current and expected salaries to Human Resources Department by clicking "Apply Now" or fax to: 2530 2218.

All information collected will be used for recruitment purpose only, only shortlisted candidates will be notified. Welcome to visit our website: http://www.bsgroup.com.hk for more information.

Job Responsibilities

To receive and execute clients’ orders in bonds, funds and structured products with counterparties;
To deal with clients and sales teams to initiate trades and execute trades, including but not limited to rate quotes, repos and other hedging derivatives;
To act as a middle office staff to support sales teams in account opening, client onboarding and servicing, and product settlement;
To handle trading and price enquiry platforms eg Ayers, Bloomberg, iFast etc;
Job Requirements

Degree holder with 3 years dealing and operational support experience in financial products (e.g. Bonds, Funds and Structured Products);
Holder of SFC License for RA1;
Hardworking and keen on learning new knowledge;
Accurate, detail-minded, responsible and self-motivated;
A team player with sound communication skills;
Proficiency in both spoken and written English and Chinese (including Mandarin);
Experience in bank dealing desk is preferable;
Immediately available is highly preferred

Attractive remuneration will be offered to the right candidate. Interested parties you may call telephone no. 3196 6253 for more details.

Personal data collected is for recruitment purpose only.

Job Duties: 

 Provide Futures quotations, handle customer inquiries and execute clients’ orders;
 Prepare daily dealing related reports and documents;
 Comply with procedures, policies and regulatory requirements.

Requirements:

NIGHT SHIFT and able to work in shift (including public holidays) is required. 
Holder of / eligible to apply for the SFC RA2 license
Preferably with 1 year working experience in global futures market;
Degree holder in Business, Finance;
Good interpersonal and communication skills (fluent in Mandarin is a must);
Efficient, task-oriented and attentive to details;
Fast response and able to work under pressure;
Immediate preferable. 

We offer competitive remuneration packages to the right candidate. Interested parties please email your resume with CURRENT SALARY & EXPECTED SALARY & AVAILABLE DATE for interview.

 (Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only)

Job Description

Deliver prompt and quality customer support services to clients and ensure smooth client onboarding;
Perform KYC to comply with SFC for account opening procedures;
Handle enquiries from frontline and internal departments;
Write press releases to promote company products;
Handle other related ad hoc tasks and assignments.

Requirements :

Bachelor Degree or above in any discipline
1-2 year’s working experience
High proficiency in both spoken and written English and Chinese and fluency in Putonghua
Excellent computer skills in MS Word, MS Excel and MS PowerPoint
Energetic, creative, well-organized and attentive to details

Job Duties :


Perform trade execution in securities, futures and options in HK and Global markets;
Handle client’s enquiries and assist in dealing operation;
Perform trade monitoring to ensure all the transactions are in compliance with SFC Hong Kong and relevant market’s regulations;
Ad hoc duties assigned by supervisor, including, but not limited to, system testing, market rehearsal and assist in new products/services rollout;
Undertake risk monitoring and perform margin call/force liquidation.



 Requirements :


Diploma/ Higher Diploma/ Degree holder in Finance, Economics or related disciplines with at least three years of relevant working experiences;
Willing to work on shifts and public holidays;
Good written command of Chinese and English, verbally fluent in Putonghua is an advantage;
Sound understanding in algo order types;
Familiar with trading systems such as i-Asia, Sharp-Point, J-Trader, NSTD and Bloomberg is a definite advantage;
Candidates with programming background is a plus;
Candidates with less experience will also be considered.

We offer attractive remuneration package and fringe benefits to the right candidate. Interested applicants please send detailed resume stating present & expected salaries and date of availability to Human Resources & Administration Department by email.

All applications will be treated in the strictest confidence and personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

Global Banking and Markets – Global Markets

Hang Seng's Global Markets business provides superior service, fully integrated solutions and 24-hour global markets coverage. Our support framework is substantial. Our advanced technologies deliver quick access to key markets. Our capital strength allows us to tailor competitively-priced solutions for specific client business around the world. We provide a full spectrum of treasury services to our customers, including foreign exchange, interest rate risk management, derivatives products, capital markets instruments, as well as market intelligence on global trends and key developments.

We are currently seeking a high caliber professional to join our department as Chief Dealer, Foreign Exchange.
  

Principal responsibilities

Manage the G7, XAU and short term interest rate tradng position in order to meet personal financial goals and ensure trading within limit;
Handle Foreign Exchange Margin operations in accordance with the business plans and policies;
A significant portion of the position is expected to be mid-shift (1345 to 2300) and provide back up to relevant team members when required;
Ensure deal executions with both internal desks and external inter-bank counterparties follow the Bank’s internal procedures and are compliant with regulations;
Provide support for new business initiative and interaction with both middle office and internal support functions;
Handle daily reports for FX department;
Perform ad hoc tasks or projects as assigned.

Requirements:

University degree in Banking, Finance, Economics or related discipline;
Minimum of five or more years of relevant work experience;
Stable, able to perform mid-shift and work responsibly in a dynamic environment;
Creative with strong analytical skill and sensitive to figures;
Proficiency in computer applications such as Bloomberg, Reuters and EBS;
Proficiency in both English and Chinese, fluency in Putonghua an advantage;
High level of customer centricity mindset with dedication to deliver exceptional quality services for customers

If you would like to explore other opportunities at Hang Seng Hong Kong, please visit www.hangseng.com/careers/ for details.


The health and safety of our employees and candidates is very important to us. Due to the current situation related to the Novel Coronavirus (2019-nCoV), we’re leveraging our digital capabilities to ensure we can continue to recruit top talent at the HSBC Group.  As your application progresses, you may be asked to use one of our digital tools to help you through your recruitment journey.  If so, one of our  Resourcing colleagues will explain how our video-interviewing technology will be used throughout the recruitment process and will be on hand to answer any questions you might have.

All information provided by applicants will be used only for recruitment purposes and will be used strictly in accordance with the Bank's personal data policies, a copy of which may be obtained by the applicant upon request. Unless otherwise instructed in writing by the applicant concerned, applicants may be considered for other suitable positions within the Bank and its related companies. The personal data of unsuccessful job applicants may be retained for a maximum of two years from the date when the job application is rejected and such data may be retained for a longer period if there is a subsisting reason that obliges the Bank to do so, after which the personal data will be destroyed.

REQUIREMENTS

Candidates with 1-3 years working experience from any industries and or potential U /DSE / Diploma / ASSO / IVE / YIJIN FRESH GRADS who are interesting in FINANCIAL FIELDS are considered;

Skillful knowledge in Excel;

Willing to learn and to do attitude, sedate under pressure, attentive, reliable, hard-working and self-disciplined;

9 hours daily SHIFT required, Mondays to Fridays only.

JOB DESCRIPTION

To monitor and control trading risks;

To quote financial products’ price and execute trading orders;

To handle clients’ enquiries;

To prepare trading documents;

NON-SALES role, no outdoor duties required.

We offer attractive benefits and remuneration package including first-tier working environment, 13 months salary, performance and discretionary bonus, 5 day work, full medical and dental insurance coverage scheme, prospective career promotion, education allowance, birthday allowance, free overseas sight-seeing trip etc. Interested parities please send your CV with current and expected salary by clicking “APPLY NOW”.

